7	  "inventory": "# Codebase Inventory — Prompt-Injection Hardening

## 1. Affected Code — Files to Create

### New: Scanner module
- `packages/plugins/clerk/src/injection-scanner.ts` — new file. The scanner module. Must be importable standalone (no clerk apparatus dependency). Exports a scan function taking a string, returning `ScanResult`. Pattern table is static regex/string matchers. Brief specifies `<10ms` for 10kB body.

### New: Scanner tests
- `packages/plugins/clerk/src/injection-scanner.test.ts` — unit tests for each pattern category (role-override, instruction-bypass, system-tag injection, path-traversal, prompt-boundary escapes). Includes 8-12 synthetic benign-corpus fixtures.

### New: Threat model doc
- `packages/plugins/clerk/docs/threat-model.md` — short enumeration of surfaces, trust classification, blast radius, recommended strictness per surface.

## 2. Affected Code — Files to Modify

### `packages/plugins/clerk/src/types.ts`
**Current state:** Defines `WritDoc`, `PostCommissionRequest`, `EditWritRequest`, `ClerkApi`, `ClerkConfig`, etc.

Changes needed:
- Add `ScanResult` type (or import from scanner module):
```ts
// Current — no scan types exist
type ScanResult = {
  clean: boolean;
  matches: Array<{ pattern: string; severity: 'low' | 'medium' | 'high'; excerpt: string }>;
};
```
- Add `injectionScan` field to `WritDoc`:
```ts
// Current WritDoc has no injectionScan field
export interface WritDoc {
  [key: string]: unknown;
  id: string;
  type: string;
  status: WritStatus;
  title: string;
  body: string;
  codex?: string;
  parentId?: string;
  createdAt: string;
  updatedAt: string;
  resolvedAt?: string;
  resolution?: string;
  // NEW: injectionScan?: { scannedAt: string; clean: boolean; matches: ... }
}
```
- Add `injectionScanMode` to `ClerkConfig`:
```ts
// Current ClerkConfig
export interface ClerkConfig {
  writTypes?: WritTypeEntry[];
  defaultType?: string;
  // NEW: injectionScanMode?: 'off' | 'flag' | 'block';
}
```

### `packages/plugins/clerk/src/clerk.ts`
**Current state:** `createClerk()` factory. The `api.post()` method (line 169-242) creates writs. The `api.edit()` method (line 327-372) patches writs. Neither performs any scanning.

Changes needed:
- Import scanner module
- In `api.post()`: scan `request.title` and `request.body` before writing. Store scan result on WritDoc. In `'block'` mode with high-severity matches, throw. In `'flag'` mode, store result but proceed. In `'off'` mode, skip scanning.
- In `api.edit()`: scan `request.title` and `request.body` (when provided) before patching. Same mode logic.
- Read `injectionScanMode` from `resolveClerkConfig()`.
- **Trust boundary**: Need a mechanism to distinguish patron-entry calls from agent-to-agent calls. Currently there is no caller identity at the API level — both tool handlers and internal code call `clerk.post()` / `clerk.edit()` identically. The brief says "the distinguishing signal is the caller identity at the tool-post site."

### `packages/plugins/clerk/src/tools/commission-post.ts`
**Current state:** (49 lines) Tool definition using `tool()` from `@shardworks/tools-apparatus`. Calls `clerk.post()` with params directly. Has `permission: 'write'`. No `callableBy` restriction — available to all callers (patron, anima, library).

```ts
export default tool({
  name: 'commission-post',
  params: {
    title: z.string(),
    body: z.string(),
    type: z.string().optional(),
    codex: z.string().optional(),
    draft: z.boolean().optional(),
    parentId: z.string().optional(),
  },
  permission: 'write',
  handler: async (params) => {
    const clerk = guild().apparatus<ClerkApi>('clerk');
    return clerk.post({ ...params });
  },
});
```

Changes needed:
- Add scanning at tool level (before calling clerk.post), OR signal to clerk.post that this is a patron-entry call.
- For CLI usage: surface matches to stderr. If `--strict` flag specified, block on medium-or-higher.
- May need a new `strict` param, or the scanning happens inside clerk.post with a "caller" signal.

### `packages/plugins/clerk/src/tools/writ-edit.ts`
**Current state:** (43 lines) Tool definition. Calls `clerk.edit()`. Has `permission: 'write'`. No `callableBy` restriction.

```ts
export default tool({
  name: 'writ-edit',
  params: {
    id: z.string(),
    title: z.string().optional(),
    body: z.string().optional(),
    type: z.string().optional(),
    codex: z.string().optional(),
  },
  permission: 'write',
  handler: async (params) => {
    const clerk = guild().apparatus<ClerkApi>('clerk');
    return clerk.edit({ ...params });
  },
});
```

Changes needed: Same pattern as commission-post — scan title/body at the patron-entry boundary.

### `packages/plugins/clerk/src/tools/index.ts`
**Current state:** Barrel re-export of all tool modules. May not need changes unless new tool files are added.

### `packages/plugins/clerk/src/index.ts`
**Current state:** Re-exports types and `createClerk`. Default export is `createClerk()`.

Changes needed: Export `ScanResult` type (and possibly the scanner function) so other surfaces can reuse it. Brief says "scanner module must be importable without pulling in the full clerk apparatus."

### `packages/plugins/clerk/src/clerk.test.ts`
**Current state:** ~1258+ lines. Uses in-memory Stacks with `MemoryBackend`, a `fakeGuild` with `fakeGuildConfig`. Tests `post()`, `show()`, `list()`, `count()`, `transition()`, `link()`, `unlink()`, `edit()`, tool handlers, config validation, kit contributions, writ-show enrichment, writ-edit tool.

Test harness pattern:
```ts
async function setup(options: SetupOptions = {}) {
  // creates MemoryBackend, stacksPlugin, clerkPlugin
  // sets up fakeGuild with fakeGuildConfig including options.clerkConfig
  // starts stacks, then clerk
}
```

Changes needed:
- Integration tests for scan at post() and edit() entry points
- Tests for each scan mode (off/flag/block)
